hughes aircraft company  wikipedia hughes aircraft company from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search hughes aircraft company hughes aircraft company logo during most of the companys first  years industry aerospace and defense defense and communications electronics fate sold to raytheon founded  in glendale california founder howard hughes headquarters culver city el segundo and westchester united states revenue b peak  owner hughes tool company  howard hughes medical institute  general motors corp  number of employees  peak  the hughes aircraft company was a major american aerospace and defense contractor founded in  by howard hughes in glendale california as a division of hughes tool company the company was known for producing among other products the hughes h hercules spruce goose aircraft the atmospheric entry probe carried by the galileo spacecraft and the aim falcon guided missile hughes aircraft was acquired by general motors from the howard hughes medical institute in  and was put under the umbrella of hughes electronics now known as directv until gm sold its assets to raytheon in  contents  history  post–world war ii  ground systems group  hughes space and communications group  hughes helicopter business  howard hughes medical institute sells hughes aircraft company  hughes electronics corporation  corporate legacy  timeline  products  air defense and air traffic control systems  aircraft  missiles  spacecraft  references  further reading  external links historyedit hughes logo adopted after the death of its founder hughes h racer hughes h hercules hughes galileo probe being deployed hughesbuilt nasa surveyor lunar lander hughes developed the aim amraam one of the worlds most advanced airtoair missiles during world war ii the company designed and built several prototype aircraft at hughes airport these included the famous hughes h hercules better known by the publics nickname for it the spruce goose the h racer d and the xf however the plants hangars at hughes airport location of presentday playa vista in the westside of los angeles california were primarily used as a branch plant for the construction of other companies designs at the start of the war hughes aircraft had only four fulltime employees—by the end the number was  post–world war iiedit hughes aircraft was one of many aerospace and defense companies which flourished in southern california during and after world war ii and was at one time the largest employer in the area by the summer of  certain politicians had become concerned about hughes alleged mismanagement of the spruce goose and the xf photo reconnaissance plane project they formed a special committee to investigate hughes which culminated in a muchfollowed senate investigation one of the first to be televised to the public despite a highly critical committee report hughes was cleared in  hughes created a new division of the company the aerospace group two hughes engineers simon ramo and dean wooldridge had new ideas on the packaging of electronics to make complete fire control systems their ma system combined signals from the aircrafts radar with a digital computer to automatically guide the interceptor aircraft into the proper position for firing missiles at the same time other teams were working with the newly formed us air force on airtoair missiles delivering the aim falcon then known as the f the mafalcon package with several upgrades was the primary interceptor weapon system of the usaf for many years lasting into the s ramo and wooldridge having failed to reach an agreement with howard hughes regarding management problems resigned in september  and founded the ramowooldridge corporation later to join thompson products to form the thompsonramowooldridge based in canoga park with hughes leasing space for nuclear research programs present day west hills canoga park the company became trw in  another aerospace company and a major competitor to hughes aircraft in  hughes aircraft co built a missile plant in tucson arizona the construction of this plant wrote david leighton in the arizona daily star newspaper was due to howard hughes’ longheld fear that his plant in culver city california was vulnerable to enemy attack because it was on the pacific coast by the end of that year the us air force had purchased the property but allowed the company to continue to run day to day operations of the site this tucson plant is still in operation under the ownership of raytheon co howard hughes donated hughes aircraft to the newly formed howard hughes medical institute hhmi in  allegedly as a way of avoiding taxes on its huge income the next year la pat hyland was hired as vice president and general manager of hughes aircraft he would ultimately become company president and ceo after howard hughes death in  under hylands guidance the aerospace group continued to diversify and become massively profitable and became a primary focus of the company the company developed radar systems electrooptical systems the first working laser aircraft computer systems missile systems ionpropulsion engines for space travel and many other advanced technologies the electronic properties information center epic of the united states was hosted at the hughes culver city library in the s epic published the multivolume handbook of electronic materials as public documents nobel laureates richard feynman and murray gellmann had hughes connections feynman would hold weekly seminars at hughes research laboratories gellmann shared an office with malcolm currie later a chairman of the board and chief executive officer at hughes aircraft greg jarvis and ronald mcnair two of the astronauts on the last flight of the space shuttle challenger were hughes alumni ground systems groupedit hughes aircraft ground systems group was located in fullerton california the facility was  million square feet and included manufacturing laboratories offices and a munson road test course it designed developed and produced the air defense systems that replaced the semi automatic defense ground environment sage in the united states with the joint surveillance system jss anfyq including norad with joint tactical information distribution system jtids and provided defense systems and air traffic control systems around the world these systems are massive and at its peak ground systems group employed  people and generated revenue in excess of  billion per year they were the largest revenue producer and with its massive systems engineering division coordinated the inclusion of products and systems from other hughes groups into the large system solutions these systems included the following ground systems group subsystems computer h consoles hmd and hmd liquid crystal large screen displays and software that set the standard for software development based on science and engineering starting with the combat grande system ground systems group was known to push technology envelopes in the computers displays local area networks human interfaces and software in their systems they also blazed the path to very highly distributed human intensive systems hughes space and communications groupedit see also boeing satellite development center hughes space and communications group and the hughes space systems division built the worlds first geosynchronous communications satellite syncom in  and followed by the first geosynchronous weather satellite ats in  later that year their surveyor  made the first soft landing on the moon as part of the leadup to the moon landings in project apollo hughes also built pioneer venus in  which performed the first extensive radar mapping of venus and the galileo probe that flew to jupiter in the s the company built nearly  percent of commercial satellites in service worldwide in  hughes helicopter businessedit main article hughes helicopters in  howard hughes redirected hughes aircrafts efforts from airplanes to helicopters the effort began in earnest in  when helicopter manufacturer kellett aircraft co sold its latest design to hughes for production the xh sky crane first flew in october  but was commercially unsuccessful in  howard hughes split the helicopter production unit from the hughes aircraft company and reconstituted it with hughes tool company calling it hughes tool companys aircraft division the aircraft division had a focus on the production of light helicopters mainly the hughes  and the oh cayusehughes  howard hughes medical institute sells hughes aircraft companyedit hughes left no will and following his death in  there were numerous claims to his estate a hughes executive and a hughes lawyer claimed they had the right to set up an executive committee to take over the running of the hhmi and its hughes aircraft subsidiary the attorney general of delaware richard r wier challenged this and filed suit in  charles m oberly continued the action when he became attorney general in  oberly stated he wished to see an independent board of trustees to ensure both that the institute fulfilled its charitable mission and that it did not continue to operate as a tax shelter in january  judge grover c brown ruled that the chancery court should appoint the trustees because hughes had not left a succession plan brown asked for both the executive committee and the attorney general’s office to submit a list of recommendations that he could approve brown approved a list in april  in january  the new board of trustees of the hhmi announced they would sell hughes aircraft either by private sale or public stock offering hughes electronics corporationedit hughes logo adopted after its new owner general motors mockup of a hughes satellite kickmotor inside the space shuttle independence similar to the one carried on sts on june   general motors was announced as the winner of a secretive five month sealedbid auction other bidders included ford motor company and boeing the purchase was completed on december   for an estimated  billion  billion in cash and the rest in  million shares of gm class h stock on december   general motors merged hughes aircraft with its delco electronics unit to form hughes electronics corporation an independent subsidiary the group then consisted of delco electronics corporation and hughes aircraft company in august of  hughes aircraft completed its purchase of general dynamics missile businesses for  million this brought the tomahawk cruise missile advanced cruise missile standard missile stinger missile phalanx closein weapon system and rolling airframe missile into hughes portfolio in  hughes electronics introduced directv the worlds first highpowered dbs service in  hughes electronics hughes space and communications division became the largest supplier of commercial satellites also in  the group purchased magnavox electronic systems from the carlyle group in  hughes electronics and panamsat agree to merge their fixed satellite services into a new publicly held company also called panamsat with hughes electronics as majority shareholder in  hughes aircraft sold its technology products division automated wire and die bonder to an investor group led by citicorp and incorporated the division as palomar technologies in  citicorp sold the bonder division to the current management team at palomar technologies in  gm transferred delco electronics to its delphi automotive systems business later that year the assets of hughes aircraft were sold to raytheon for  billion the remaining companies remained under the hughes electronics name and within gm in  the boeing company purchased three units within hughes electronics corp hughes space and communications co hughes electron dynamics and spectrolab inc in addition to hughes electronics interest in hrl the companys primary research laboratory the four joined boeing satellite systems a company subsidiary later becoming the satellite development center part of boeing integrated defense systems in  the remaining parts of hughes electronics directv directv latin america panamsat hughes network systems were purchased by news corporation from gm and renamed the directv group corporate legacyedit the wide range of science and technology developed by hughes aircraft never included medical applications because the company was owned by the howard hughes medical institute hhmi this restriction was imposed to avoid even the appearance of a conflict of interest however the money provided to hhmi by hughes aircraft led to major improvements to the medical field from genetics cancer research to producing doctors who provide care to millions of people it is important to note that hughes developed the modern medical bed as a direct result of his hospital internment timelineedit hughes logo adopted during the period  between the sales of portions of the company to raytheon and boeing each subsidiary of hughes space and communications company placed their name at the bottom of the logo  howard hughes formed hughes aircraft company as a division of hughes tool company  hughes formed the aerospace group within the company divided into hughes space and communications group hughes space systems division  hughes aircraft opened missile plant in tucson arizona  the howard hughes medical institute hhmi was formed and hughes aircraft reformed as a subsidiary of the foundation the internal revenue service unsuccessfully challenged its charitable status which made it taxexempt  hughes formed its helicopter division aircraft division  the first laser was produced at hughes research laboratories by theodore maiman  hughes research laboratories completed their move to malibu california  hughes sold the tool division of hughes tool company his remaining interests were transferred to the newly formed holding company the summa corporation this included toolco aircraft and hughes property and other businesses  toolco aircraft became hughes helicopters  howard hughes died at the age of  leaving no will  the summa corporation sold hughes helicopters to mcdonnell douglas for  million it was soon renamed mcdonnell douglas helicopters  the delaware court of chancery appointed eight trustees to the howard hughes medical institute they decided to sell hughes aircraft  the hhmi sold hughes aircraft to general motors for  billion this was merged with gms delco electronics to form hughes electronics corporation this group then consisted of delco electronics corporation hughes aircraft company  hughes aircraft company acquired macom telecommunications to form hughes network systems  hughes electronics introduced directv  hughes space and communications company became the worlds biggest supplier of commercial satellites  hughes electronics acquired magnavox electronic systems from the carlyle group  hughes aircraft acquired caelink caelink was part of the original company founded by edwin link inventor of the flight simulator  hughes electronics and panamsat agreed to merge their fixed satellite services into a new publicly held company also called panamsat with hughes electronics as majority shareholder  gm transferred delco electronics from hughes electronics to its delphi automotive systems delphi became independent in   the aerospace and defense operations of hughes electronics hughes aircraft merged with raytheon raytheon also acquired one half of the hughes research laboratories  hughes space and communications company remained independent until  when it was purchased by boeing and became boeing satellite development center boeing purchased one third of the hrl laboratories llc which was then coowned by boeing gm and raytheon  the remaining parts of hughes electronics directv directv latin america panamsat and hughes network systems were purchased by newscorp and renamed the directv group  newscorp sold panamsat to kohlberg kravis roberts  co kkr in august   director martin scorsese used the hughes aircraft stage in playa vista to film the motioncapture sequences in the film the aviator  skyterra communications inc completed its purchase of  controlling interest in hughes network systems from the directv group in january  productsedit air defense and air traffic control systemsedit tactical air weapons control system joint surveillance system german air defense ground environment geadge integrated nato air defense system nato air defence ground environment nadge  nspa airborne early warning  ground environment integration segment aegis canadian air traffic control system korean air traffic control system joint tactical information distribution system jtids aircraftedit hughes d hughes h hughes h hercules hughes xf missilesedit aim falcon aim falcon aim falcon aim phoenix aim amraam agm maverick bgm tow brazo spacecraftedit hs anik satellite jarvis rocket magellan spacecraft morelos satellite system paksat satellite pioneer program pioneer venus multiprobe pioneer venus orbiter surveyor program surveyor  surveyor  surveyor  surveyor  surveyor  surveyor  surveyor  referencesedit  hughes built his h racer in a hangar at the grand central air terminal in glendale california by july  hughes aircraft had relocated its flight line to culver city california in the playa del rey wetlands alongside ballona creek  httpwwwcentennialofflightnetessayaerospacehughesaerohtm  parker dana t building victory aircraft manufacturing in the los angeles area in world war ii pp – cypress ca   httpwwwbritannicacomebcheckedtopichugheselectronicscorporation  parker dana t building victory aircraft manufacturing in the los angeles area in world war ii p  cypress ca   httpaerofilescomhhtml  a b judy rumerman the hughes companies us centennial of flight commission retrieved    parker dana t building victory aircraft manufacturing in the los angeles area in world war ii pp  cypress ca    trw canoga park  leighton david  street smarts tucsons biggest manufacturing plant was almost built in phoenix arizona daily star lee enterprises p  retrieved    winslow ron  virginia lab